-- Edwards Says Cnooc’s Nexen Bid Will Probably Be Approved
-- B y   A n d r e w   M a y e d a
-- 2012-09-25T15:40:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-25/edwards-says-cnooc-s-nexen-bid-will-probably-be-approved.html
Cnooc Ltd. (883) ’s $15.1 billion bid for
Calgary-based  Nexen Inc. (NXY)  will probably be approved by the
Canadian government,  Canadian Natural Resources Ltd. (CNQ)  Chairman N.
Murray Edwards said.  Speaking at a conference in Ottawa, Edwards said Cnooc will
have to decide if any conditions that the Canadian government
may place on the deal would be acceptable.  To contact the reporter on this story:
